# .templatesyncignore
# The human-readable manifest of "project-owned" paths that are NEVER overwritten
# when syncing updates from the bc-alm-template repository: your real code and the
# values written by the one-time initializer. scripts/Update-FromTemplate.ps1 (run
# locally, and by .github/workflows/template-sync.yml) enforces this same set, and
# additionally honors the 'sync' block in template.config.json:
#   * customizationsPath - where agents/skills/instructions live (root or app/)
#   * updateModels        - when false, your agent 'model:' choices are re-applied
#   * updateExtensions    - when false, your .vscode/extensions.json is kept
#   * updateInstructions  - when false, your .github/instructions is kept
#   * include             - per-category switches (metaDocs, referenceDocs, issueOps,
#                           specs, prTemplate); a category set to false is never
#                           copied or re-added
#
# Everything NOT listed here (and not excluded by a sync toggle) is "template-managed"
# and will be refreshed from the template (agents, skills, instructions, scripts,
# meta-docs, workflows). Syntax is .gitignore-style.

# --- Your AL source (the sample app is only a starting point) ---
app/
test/

# --- One-time initializer output / configured values ---
template.config.json
PROJECT.md
.github/copilot-instructions.md
.vscode/launch.json
.vscode/mcp.json
.vscode/settings.json
*.code-workspace

# --- Your specs (keep the blank template, ignore real specs) ---
specs/*
!specs/_TEMPLATE/
!specs/_TEMPLATE/**

# --- Repo identity / meta you own ---
README.md
LICENSE
.git*

# --- Template-repo-only files (a derived repo doesn't need these; the initializer
#     removes them during cleanup, and this keeps sync from re-adding them) ---
CONTRIBUTING.md
bootstrap.ps1
scripts/Install-IntoExistingRepo.ps1

# --- The sync workflow keeps updating itself; that's intentional, so it is
#     NOT ignored. Remove the leading '#' below if you want to pin your own copy.
# .github/workflows/template-sync.yml
